h2. @ctioga2@ prerequisites

To have a working copy of @ctioga2@, you need :

* "Ruby":http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/;
* a LaTeX distribution, such as "TeXLive":http://www.tug.org/texlive/;
* a recent version of "Tioga":http://tioga.rubyforge.org.

h2. Installation

h3. Tarballs

Download the latest tarball of @ctioga2@ at the 
"download page":http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=8218. Let us assume
the file is named @ctioga2-0.2.tar.bz2@. 

First, extract the tarball this way:

<pre class='examples-cmdline'>
tar xvjf ctioga2-0.2.tar.gz
</pre>

Then @cd@ to the directory created. Here, it is @ctioga2-0.2@:

<pre class='examples-cmdline'>
cd ctioga2-0.2
</pre>

@ctioga2@ is using
"@setup.rb@":http://i.loveruby.net/en/projects/setup/doc/usage.html
for handling its installation. In short, run this command as root.

<pre class='examples-cmdline'>
ruby setup.rb
</pre>

h3. Gems

Gems are published for @ctioga2@. Installing them is just a matter of
running:

<pre class='examples-cmdline'>
gem install ctioga2
</pre>

h3. SVN repository

The code of @ctioga2@ is developed in a 
"SVN repository":http://rubyforge.org/scm/?group_id=8218. To make use of
it, get a "SVN client":http://subversion.tigris.org/ and get a working
copy of the repository using this command:

<pre class='examples-cmdline'>
svn checkout http://ctioga2.rubyforge.org/svn/trunk/ctioga2
</pre>

Then use the instructions as above for the installation using the tarball.
